
@Transactional
When a method is marked with @Transactional, spring automatically creates a transaction around that method,
it ensures that every transaction is treated as an atomic operation,and if any one of them fails in between
then all of the above transaction gets rolled back.It ensures the consistency of the data.


Q9.Which method on the session object can be used to remove an object from the cache?
evict()method is used to remove a particular object from the cache associated with the session.

clear()method is used to delete all the objects from the cache.